From: Abrikosi4 <116901278+Abrikosi4@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] arm64: dts: qcom: sunfish: enable QG fuel gauge + SMB2 charger

Wire up the PM6150 QGauge (fuel gauge) and SMB2 charger so userspace gets
battery capacity/voltage/current/temperature and charge status/online.
Both nodes exist in pm6150.dtsi but are disabled and need a monitored-battery;
add a simple-battery describing the Pixel 4a's 3140 mAh cell and enable them.

Signed-off-by: Abrikosi4 <116901278+Abrikosi4@users.noreply.github.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm7150-google-sunfish.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm7150-google-sunfish.dts
@@ -651,6 +651,26 @@
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
+/ {
+	battery: battery {
+		compatible = "simple-battery";
+		charge-full-design-microamp-hours = <3140000>;
+		voltage-min-design-microvolt = <3400000>;
+		voltage-max-design-microvolt = <4400000>;
+		constant-charge-current-max-microamp = <2000000>;
+	};
+};
+
+&pm6150_charger {
+	monitored-battery = <&battery>;
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&pm6150_qgauge {
+	monitored-battery = <&battery>;
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
 &pm6150_typec {
 	vdd-vbus-supply = <&pm6150_vbus>;
 	vdd-pdphy-supply = <&vdda_usb_hs_3p1>;
